NOTICE — vendored Zscaler documentation
=========================================

The files in this directory are documentation artifacts published by Zscaler,
Inc., retrieved from help.zscaler.com. They are included in this repository
as a pinned bibliography: our `references/*.md` make claims about Zscaler
behavior and cite specific files here as the primary source. Committing them
keeps those citations reproducible across machines and clones.

This repository does not claim authorship of these artifacts. All rights are
retained by Zscaler, Inc. They are included here in good faith as reference
material accompanying a derivative work (the `references/` distillation).

If you are Zscaler, Inc. and would prefer we cite URLs rather than vendor
these artifacts, open an issue on this repository and we will remove them.

Sources
-------

The canonical published versions of each artifact live at:

- help.zscaler.com (most articles, paths like /zia/..., /zpa/..., and
  /zscaler-deployments-operations/...)
- help.zscaler.com/downloads/... (CSVs, checklists, reference architecture PDFs)

Specific URLs are recorded in the `sources:` YAML frontmatter of each
`references/*.md` file that cites a given artifact, along with the fetch date.

Retrieval method
----------------

- PDFs named in Title_Snake_Case (e.g. `URL_Filtering_Deployment_and_Operations_Guide.pdf`)
  were obtained via the "Print PDF" export on help.zscaler.com articles, which
  renders JavaScript-generated content to PDF.
- PDFs named in kebab-case (e.g. `ssl-inspection-checklist.pdf`, `zpa-app-segmentation-refarch.pdf`)
  and CSV files were downloaded directly from help.zscaler.com/downloads/...
  via HTTP, which serves these static assets without JavaScript.

Both naming conventions coexist; we do not normalize filenames to avoid
breaking the `sources:` references that point at them.
